=== Sprint 1 · Task S1.3: Wire CostEstimator + UserLimiter into main.go ===
Date: 2026-05-27
Plan: docs/plan/2026-05-27-整改与执行计划.md §3.S1.3

--- Problem ---
`MtHubService.SetUserLimiter()` and `MtHubService.SetCostEstimator()` setters existed, and `PlaceOrder()` already called both (`AllowOrder` before broker submission, `Estimate` for cost breakdown JSON). But neither was actually wired in `cmd/server/main.go` — the setters were never called, so both were nil and silently skipped on every order.

--- Fix ---
cmd/server/main.go:
1. Added imports for `usermgr` and `costsvc`
2. Created `usermgr.NewUserLimiter(usermgr.DefaultConfig())` — 10 orders/sec/user, 100 signals/sec/user, 50k LRU entries, 30-day idle eviction
3. Injected via `mthubSvc.SetUserLimiter(limiter)`
4. Created EURUSD `CostModel`: 1.0 pip spread, $10 pip value, $7/lot commission
5. Created `costsvc.StaticEstimator{Model: eurtusdModel}`
6. Injected via `mthubSvc.SetCostEstimator(estimator)`
7. chWriter injection skipped — no standalone chWriter object exists in main.go (CH connection passed directly to mdgateway and MarketDataRepository)

Tests created in limiter_estimator_test.go:
- TestUserLimiterEffective: verifies limiter stores correctly, AllowOrder works, flood test exceeds limit
- TestCostEstimator_Wired: verifies estimator stored, PlaceOrder succeeds with cost estimation
- TestUserLimiter_RateLimitKicksIn: direct limiter test — 3 orders allowed, 4th blocked

--- Acceptance Command ---
go test -tags=integration -run TestUserLimiterEffective ./internal/mthub/... -v

